runs.comm: shapes himself for a big one with that high backlift but the ball isn't there to hit, bowled on a good length on middle, pushed to mid-on
spat off the pitch, a scorcher that, slightly back of a length on the off stump and shot off to evade the outside edge as he tried to defend that off the back foot

superb stuff, stopped a bit on Warner, caught him by surprise as it zipped off the wicket, caught the outside edge and flew towards third man, he tried to play that down with soft hands but was a little late on the shot, no damage done though
similar delivery but to the right hander this time, Clarke dealt with it well, unlike Warner he backed away from it
missed opportunity, short and wide, there to cut, he tries to do exactly that but the ball moves away at the right moment to have him reaching for that one
short of a good length outside off, dabbed wide of Duminy at cover for a quick single
starts off with a wide but bowled at a decent pace there, had Clarke reaching for a cut, missed it obviously, hence the wide
much closer to the off stump and bowled a touch fuller, closes the face to push that short of mid-on for a quick single
good pace, short of a good length on middle and leg at 143 kmph, defended off the back foot towards midwicket
slower through the air and erred in length there, full on the pads, clipped away elegantly to fine leg

well stopped, full on the off stump, Clarke plays a delightful drive back to the bowler, Parnell bends low, it catches him on the foot, and prevents a couple of runs, did well to get his body behind that one

timber! Parnell gets one, fullish on the off stump, held its line, Clarke had decided he would go after that one, bowled at 143 kmph, he makes room to smash that over extra cover, misses and the stumps take a beating!
full on the off stump, stands his ground and dispatches it over mid-on for a one bounce four, got under it nicely there, meaty length ball that got the treatment
short of a good length on middle, mistimes a pull wide of fine leg for a couple, would have wanted to get that much squarer
slower ball, misdirected though, well outside off stump and it's given a wide
back of a length on the off stump, dragged wide of mid-on for a single
shuffles to work it away behind square, is struck on the pads, would have been going down anyway, gets a leg bye
slower ball bowled short on leg stump, turned away towards square leg for a single
short of a good length outside off, punched firmly wide of cover where Duminy dives full length to his right to stop that and prevent a couple of runs
good length on middle and off, defended off the front foot towards cover

poor shot really, hit a good length on middle and leg, Ponting stayed in his crease and tried to clear mid-on, wasn't to the pitch at all, ended up mistiming it towards Johan Botha who ran a few steps back and pouched it gleefully.
held it back a little, pitched it a little short outside off, punched off the back foot to cover, well timed but straight to the fielder
low full toss on the off stump, steps wide and tries to force it through the off-side field, finds the cover fielder but scrambles a single
shaping away from the right hander, full outside off, almost yorker length, dug out between point and cover, the bowling change has paid off, at least until now
good over, bowled on the off stump, giving him no room, plays that with an angled bat towards point
on middle and off, dropped into the off side short of mid-off for a single
shot! Short and wide, makes room, bends a little and cuts it away behind point, third man had no chance there

run out appeal, dropped into the off side towards cover and Warner rushes in for a single, he's halfway down the pitch at the non-striker's end, the fielder returns the throw to Parnell who flicks it onto the stumps, Warner has dived full stretch but his bat appears to be in the air as he tries to slide it back into the crease. Too much doubt there, and the umpire gives the batsman the benefit of the doubt
full on leg stump, tries to flick it away fine, misses, would have gone down
bowled on a good length at 124.1 kmph on the off stump, tries to drive it wide of mid-off, gets a thick inside edge towards mid -on
full length on the off stump, driven crisply wide of Amla at mid-off where he dives to his right and keeps them down to a single
back of a length on the off stump, gets the treatment, pulled away powerfully behind square, sped off the bat
tried to turn it away fine, hit high on the pads and ball drops just wide of the stumps, they sneak a quick single
yorker length on the off stump, dug out wide of mid-off for a single
struck well, attempted yorker again but Warner gets forward, converts it into a full toss and drills that down the ground wide of mid-on
change of pace but Warner picked the slower one, landed full on middle, he took a step forward, got under it nicely and lofted it cleanly over the long-on boundary
better, bowled on a good length on middle, worked up good pace, defended to mid-on off the back foot
full on middle and leg, tossed up, driven straight to midwicket
on middle and off, gets outside the line and turns it away wide of short fine for a single
back of a length outside off, cut away behind point for a couple, came back well for the second there

quicker through the air, landed on a good length on middle and spun away sharply, Warner came forward to defend, was beaten by the spin, caught the outside edge and the ball rolls over the third-man boundary
round the wicket now, on middle and off, turned away to midwicket
quicker and full on the off stump, slaps it back to the bowler, mistimed it there
misfield at extra cover, driven straight to him but AB de Villiers gets a bad bounce, they get a couple between long-off and deep cover
flighted on middle, driven down the ground towards long-on where some lax fielding allows them to come back for the second
welcome runs, full outside off, Hussey makes room and smashes that over the extra-cover boundary, fiercely struck, a flat six that
wristy, full on middle, drives that subcontinental-style towards long-on
attemps a slog-sweep, mistimes it straight to midwicket, there to hit, a length ball that but couldn't connect it well
full on leg stump but fired in quick, he can just dig it out and salvage a single towards long-on
well bowled, bowling fairly quick here, full on leg stump, drives it inside out to cover
full on middle and leg, driven to Amla at long-on
well struck but there's cover, flat on the off stump, drilled down the ground but Amla's there at long-off
goes for it, full on leg stump, tries to heave it over midwicket, mistimes it but still manages a couple, Duminy runs well to his left, slides and prevents any further damage
good length on the off stump, driven to long-off
that's disappeared, timely hit, flighted on the off stump, much slower through the air, Hussey's eyes light up, he gets under it and dismisses it over the long-on boundary
excellent reflexes by Peterson! Bowled full on the off stump, Warner picks the length and swats it firmly but straight towards the bowler, Peterson reacts well, bends down and takes it low.

run out, Australia are struggling now, turned away towards short fine where the fielder rockets in a powerful throw at the non-strikers end, Micheal Hussey has already set off for the single but isn't quick enough, dives full length but a direct hit catches him well short of his ground
tossed up on middle and leg, driven to long-off
full on middle and leg, driven back to the bowler
flighted on middle and off, struck firmly but back to Peterson

he's thrown it away! Flighted on the off stump, lands on a good length, Haddin lofts it lazily, no intent whatsoever in that stroke, finds Albie Morkel at long-off positioned exactly for some poor batting like that
tossed up on the off stump, pushed off the front foot to cover
turned away off the back foot towards square leg
driven down the ground to long-on to get off the mark
low full toss on the off stump, bunts it to cover, a bump ball that, creates some excitement in the crowd
flighted on the off stump, comes down the track and pushes it to long-on
gets on the back foot and punches it through the covers for a single
short of a length outside off, gets back and slaps it to long-off, spun away there but he handled it well
full on middle and off, drives it through the line to long-off
back of a length on the off stump, tries to pull it away over midwicket, mistimes it back to the bowler
fired in on the leg stump, turned away straight to short fine
the frustration grows, short outside off, bunts it straight to cover, fails to beat the fielder there
almost but gets away with it, lofted straight towards long-off but it falls well short of the fielder, thay have time to get back for the second
full on the off stump, makes room and drives it through the gap between long-off and deep cover, gets a couple for his efforts
maintains a fullish length, outside off again, square-driven towards deep cover
held it back this time, back of a length outside off, run down to third man for a single
full on middle and off, driven back to the bowler, bump ball again and crowd wastes some more energy with all its oohs and aahs
superbly hit, not even to the pitch but just played through the line, good length outside off, he gave himself some room there and just chipped it over extra cover
much fuller, strikes it down the ground towards long-on
flighted ball bowled full on the leg stump, driven to long-on
well fielded, struck back towards the bowler, Botha dives to his left and saves a single
short of a length on the off stump, much slower through the air, punched straight to cover
good stuff, saw the batsman make some room there and fired it full, dug out towards long-on
full toss, fails to cash in, on middle, swats it away towards deep square leg
low full toss outside off, much quicker, driven to long-off, excellent over
almost, short of a length outside off, cut away uppishly towards Gibbs at point who dives to his left to pluck that but it falls just short
on middle and leg, worked away wide of midwicket for a single
goes for it but fails to connect well, drives it uppishly towards long-off
short of a length outside off, makes room , is deceived by the slower one, slaps it back over the bowler's head but it's completely mistimed, lands safely between long-off and long-on
gets hold of it this time, bowled round the wicket, full outside off, reaches for it and creams it over the extra-cover boundary, went about 10-15 rows into the crowd
back of a length on middle, turned away between square leg and midwicket for a single, keeps the strike
slogged away and it's over the ropes, full and straight on the off stump, bowled quick, heaves it over the deep midwicket boundary, reaches his 50 in style
short of a good length on leg stump, comes down the track, gets an inside edge towards short fine
short on the off stump, pushed off the back foot to over, was al most fone in by the flight there, failed to pick it
quick on middle, yorker length, dug out back to the bowler

attempts something similar this time but it's full and meaty on middle, White gets hold of this, was waiting for it for a long time and finally connects it well enough to clear deep midwicket, a typical limited-overs slog that
identical stroke but not the result, struck it well but the ball was bowled much slower through the air, heaved it, but straight to deep midwicket where Duminy judges it to perfection
full on middle and leg, gets his feet out of the way and drives it to long-on
back of a length on the off stump and nipped back in, dropped into the leg side, no single there
back of a length on middle, plays a short-arm pull towards long-on
straying down the leg side, given a wide, the first one in a long time
full on middle and leg, chipped over midwicket but all they can manage is a single
attempted yorker, ends up as a full toss on leg stump, flicked away to deep square leg

wow, that was something! Full on middle, length ball, so he pays for bowling that wide, Hussey gets stuck into that one, lofts it high and AB de Villiers at long on takes it over his head but trips over the boundary ropes, took forever to come down but poor ball by Albie. An excellent catch there, took it with one hand, but what a waste in the end
good length on the off stump, chipped wide of long-on for a couple
full outside off, slashes hard, it's a slower one, gets a thick edge towards third man
Hussey's the man, full outside off, in the slot, makes room and caresses it wide of a diving extra cover
good comeback, yorker on leg stump, saw him making room there but the batsman is equal to the task, digs it out wide of deep square leg for a couple
slower ball bowled full on middle, slogged over midwicket, Duminy dives full length to his left and drags that back just inside the ropes, two taken
Hussey's got Australia back in this, full on middle, shuffles outside of and tickles that well wide of short fine for a boundary
lucky! Good length outside off, goes for a flowing drive through the off side, gets a thin edge just pas the leg stump to the fine-leg boundary
short of a good length outside off, it's moving away as he tries to cut, misses, and is called a wide
good length on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on
length ball on the off stump, gets away with it, Hussey plays it along the ground to long-on
deceived him with the slower one there, good length outside off and Johnson is already through with his attempted slog over midwicket, misses
beaten again, full outside off, tries to cross-bat that over midwicket again, misses and the frustration is writ large on his face
bowled 'im! Good stuff from Parnell, in the blockhole on middle, Johnson tries to dig it out on the leg side but is a little too late in bringing his bat down, misses and the stumps are rattled
short of a good length outside off, makes room and creams it to deep cover
good shot, full outside off, makes room and slices that away behind point for a boundary
slower ball bowled on a good length on middle and leg, dabs it on the leg side towards square leg for a single
shot of the day, length ball again but had to be dealt with, overpitched on middle, moved away and drilled it past a diving cover to bisect the gap between long-off and deep cover

what a knock! Picked the slower one there, ended up landing full on the off stump, waited for it and smashed it away over the long-on boundary, goes miles into the crowd and Australia have posted a competitive score here
struck fiercely but straight to the deep-cover fielder, raced off the bat but no damage done
